  <description>Stems dimorphic, flowering stems erect or ascending, stolons prostrate, rooting
        nodally, glabrous or sparsely hirsute, not bulbous-based. Tuberous roots absent. Basal
        leaves simple and undivided, blades oblong to cordate or circular, 0.7-3.8 × 0.8-3.2 cm,
        base rounded to cordate, margins crenate or crenate-serrate, apex rounded. Flowers:
        receptacle hispid or glabrous; sepals spreading, 2.5-6 × 1.5-3 mm, glabrous; petals 5,
        yellow, 2-7 × 1-3 mm. Heads of achenes long-ovoid or cylindric, 6-12 × 4-5(-9) mm; achenes
        1-1.4(-2.2) × 0.8-1.2 mm, glabrous; beak persistent, conic, straight, 0.1-0.2 mm. 2n =
        16.</description>
  <phenology>Flowering late spring-summer (May-Sep)</phenology>
